M||tx|---
M||name|using-git-worktrees
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Use when starting feature work that needs isolation from current workspace or before executing implementation plans - creates isolated git worktrees w/ smart directory selection and safety verification
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[qa, testing, debugging, qual, lint, code-rv, pulse, productivity]
M||tx|---
M|Over|tx|Git worktrees cr isolated workspaces sharing the same repository, allowing work on multiple branches simultaneously w/o switching.
M|Over|**Co|** Systematic directory selection + safety verification = reliable isolation.
M|Over|**An|** "I'm using the using-git-worktrees skill to set up an isolated workspace."
M|Dire|Foll|
M|1. C|tx|```bash
M|Chec|tx|ls -d .worktrees 2>/dv/null     # Preferred (hidden)
M|Chec|tx|ls -d worktrees 2>/dv/null      # Alternative
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Chec|**If|** Use that directory. If both exist, `.worktrees` wins.
M|2. C|tx|```bash
M|2. C|tx|grep -i "worktree.*director" CLAUDE.md 2>/dv/null
M|2. C|tx|```
M|2. C|**If|** Use it w/o asking.
M|3. A|If n|
M|3. A|tx|```
M|3. A|tx|No worktree directory found. Where shd I cr worktrees?
M|3. A|tx|1. .worktrees/ (project-local, hidden)
M|3. A|tx|2. ~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/<project-name>/ (global location)
M|3. A|tx|Which wld you prefer?
M|3. A|tx|```
M|For |**MU|**
M|For |tx|```bash
M|Chec|tx|git check-ignore -q .worktrees 2>/dv/null \|\| git check-ignore -q worktrees 2>/dv/null
M|Chec|tx|```
M|Chec|**If|**
M|Chec|Per |
M|Chec|tx|1. Add appropriate line to .gitignore
M|Chec|tx|2. Commit the change
M|Chec|tx|3. Proceed w/ worktree creation
M|Chec|**Wh|** Prevents accidentally committing worktree contents to repository.
M|For |tx|No .gitignore verification needed - outside project entirely.
M|1. D|tx|```bash
M|1. D|tx|project=$(basename "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)")
M|1. D|tx|```
M|2. C|tx|```bash
M|Dete|tx|case $LOCATION in
M|Dete|tx|.worktrees\|worktrees)
M|Dete|tx|path="$LOCATION/$BRANCH_NAME"
M|Dete|tx|;;
M|Dete|tx|~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/*)
M|Dete|tx|path="~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/$project/$BRANCH_NAME"
M|Dete|tx|;;
M|Dete|tx|esac
M|Crea|tx|git worktree add "$path" -b "$BRANCH_NAME"
M|Crea|tx|cd "$path"
M|Crea|tx|```
M|3. R|Auto|
M|3. R|tx|```bash
M|Node|tx|if [ -f pk.json ]; then npm install; fi
M|Rust|tx|if [ -f Cargo.toml ]; then cargo bd; fi
M|Pyth|tx|if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi
M|Pyth|tx|if [ -f pyproject.toml ]; then poetry install; fi
M|Go|tx|if [ -f go.mod ]; then go mod download; fi
M|Go|tx|```
M|4. V|Run |
M|4. V|tx|```bash
M|Exam|tx|npm tst
M|Exam|tx|cargo tst
M|Exam|tx|pytest
M|Exam|tx|go tst ./...
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|**If|** rp failures, ask whether to proceed or investigate.
M|Exam|**If|** rp ready.
M|5. R|tx|```
M|5. R|tx|Worktree ready at <full-path>
M|5. R|tx|Tests passing (<N> tests, 0 failures)
M|5. R|tx|Ready to im <feature-name>
M|5. R|tx|```
M|Quic|tx|\| Situation \| Action \|
M|Quic|tx|\|-----------\|--------\|
M|Quic|tx|\| `.worktrees/` exists \| Use it (verify ignored) \|
M|Quic|tx|\| `worktrees/` exists \| Use it (verify ignored) \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Both exist \| Use `.worktrees/` \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Neither exists \| Check CLAUDE.md → Ask us \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Directory not ignored \| Add to .gitignore + commit \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Tests fail during baseline \| rp failures + ask \|
M|Quic|tx|\| No pk.json/Cargo.toml \| Skip dependency install \|
M|Skip|- **|** Worktree contents get tracked, pollute git status
M|Skip|- **|** Always use `git check-ignore` before creating project-local worktree
M|Assu|- **|** Creates inconsistency, violates project conventions
M|Assu|- **|** Follow priority: existing > CLAUDE.md > ask
M|Proc|- **|** Can't distinguish new bugs from pre-existing issues
M|Proc|- **|** rp failures, get explicit permission to proceed
M|Hard|- **|** Breaks on projects using different tools
M|Hard|- **|** Auto-detect from project files (pk.json, etc.)
M|Exam|tx|```
M|Exam|You|I'm using the using-git-worktrees skill to set up an isolated workspace.
M|Exam|tx|[Check .worktrees/ - exists]
M|Exam|tx|[Verify ignored - git check-ignore confirms .worktrees/ is ignored]
M|Exam|[Cre|git worktree add .worktrees/auth -b feature/auth]
M|Exam|tx|[Run npm install]
M|Exam|tx|[Run npm tst - 47 passing]
M|Exam|tx|Worktree ready at /us/jesse/myproject/.worktrees/auth
M|Exam|tx|Tests passing (47 tests, 0 failures)
M|Exam|tx|Ready to im auth feature
M|Exam|tx|```
